vulnerabilities.title: Prototype pollution in set-in
vulnerabilities.description: Prototype pollution vulnerability in 'set-in' versions 1.0.0 through 2.0.0 allows attacker to cause a denial of service and may lead to remote code execution.

vulnerabilities.title: Prototype Pollution in set-in
vulnerabilities.description: The package set-in before 2.0.3 is vulnerable to Prototype Pollution via the `setIn` method, as it allows an attacker to merge object prototypes into it. **Note:** This vulnerability derives from an incomplete fix of [CVE-2020-28273](https://security.snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-SETIN-1048049)
